      <section id="overview" class="section" data-reveal>
        <h2>📌 Project overview</h2>
        <div class="grid two">
          <div>
            <h3>Problem</h3>
            <p>Watsons' in-store beauty service booking experience relied on region buttons and WhatsApp chat to arrange beauty services. This created low awareness of in-store services, high no-show rates, and limited engagement with Watsons' beauty expertise and product offerings.</p>
            <h3>Objective</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Replace chat with a guided, self-serve booking flow</strong> (service → location → artist → date).</li>
              <li><strong>Engage new users</strong> through redesigned page layout and improved user experience.</li>
              <li><strong>Introduce in-store services</strong> with clear service descriptions, benefits, and booking flows.</li>
              <li><strong>Invite participation</strong> in beauty services through compelling content and seamless booking experience.</li>
              <li><strong>Provide beauty education</strong> with skincare information, tips, and expert guidance.</li>
              <li><strong>Reduce no-show rates</strong> through better communication, reminders, and policy transparency.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>My role</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Page redesign</strong> - Complete visual and UX overhaul to improve engagement and service discovery.</li>
              <li><strong>User engagement strategy</strong> - Design flows to attract and convert new users to in-store services.</li>
              <li><strong>Service introduction</strong> - Create clear, compelling presentations of beauty services and their benefits.</li>
              <li><strong>Educational content design</strong> - Structure beauty and skincare information for easy consumption and trust-building.</li>
              <li><strong>No-show reduction</strong> - Implement booking confirmation, reminder systems, and clear policy communication.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        
      </section>

      

      <section id="challenge" class="section" data-reveal>
        <h2>💪🏻 Challenge</h2>
        <p class="muted">The AS‑IS experience relied on region buttons and chat‑based booking, which created friction and limited visibility into real‑time availability.</p>
