      <section id="reflection" class="section" data-reveal>
        <h2>💭 Reflection</h2>
        <ul class="bullets">
          <li><strong>Complex bookings</strong> — Support for back‑to‑back multi‑service bundles and built‑in buffer times simplified planning and reduced staff hand‑offs.</li>
          <li><strong>Group scenarios</strong> — Two‑person bookings with synchronized slots balanced availability and store capacity.</li>
          <li><strong>Policy transparency</strong> — Late arrival and no‑show rules were surfaced inline to prevent surprises and reduce disputes.</li>
          <li><strong>Offline tolerance</strong> — Preserved selections and safe retries ensured progress wasn't lost during weak connections.</li>
          <li><strong>Accessibility</strong> — Larger tap targets, keyboard navigation, and reduced motion options made the flow more inclusive.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="muted">Next explorations: group bookings beyond two people, deeper loyalty integration, and in‑store queue visibility.</p>
